description._content: Catalog #: 09_01262 Title: Captain Dorris Gurley Special Collection Photo San Diego California Additional Information: Military inspection with two Vought VE-7 aircraft in line. Handwritten inscription ""(Dorris) Gurley shaking hands with Commander Robert P. Molten, San Diego California"", Dorris Gurley joined the U.S. Navy in 1919 aged 25. His active naval service finished in April 1946, when he retired with the rank of Captain. During World War II he commanded the naval air stations at Ottumwa, Iowa and later at Bunker Hill, Indiana, Corporation Name: Lewis & Vought Coporation Tags: Captain Dorris Gurley Special Collection Photo San Diego California,Â 1922,Â Lewis & Vought Coporation Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
